Linux

open shell

1. start mongodb
    1.1 `sudo service mongod start`
    1.2 mongo

2.db.gethelp() : command will tell u all the methods

3.exit : command simply quits mongo server

4. show dbs : config for ur local db

5. use testDB : switches to database

6. db.createCollection("contacts") : create collections in db

7. show collections;

8. db.users.insert({"name" : "xyz" });

9. db.users.find();

8. db.dropDatabase() : delete database
